## 10. Testing Checklist

### 10.1 Manual Testing (Required)

**iOS:**
- [ ] Enable VoiceOver (Settings → Accessibility → VoiceOver)
- [ ] Navigate through app using swipe gestures
- [ ] Activate elements with double-tap
- [ ] Verify all labels are meaningful
- [ ] Check focus order is logical

**Android:**
- [ ] Enable TalkBack (Settings → Accessibility → TalkBack)
- [ ] Navigate and test similarly to iOS

**Web:**
- [ ] Navigate using Tab key only
- [ ] Verify all interactive elements are reachable
- [ ] Check focus indicators are visible
- [ ] Test with screen reader (VoiceOver, NVDA)

---

### 10.2 Automated Testing

**Accessibility linting:**

```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y
```

**.eslintrc.js:**
```javascript
module.exports = {
  plugins: ['jsx-a11y'],
  extends: ['plugin:jsx-a11y/recommended'],
}
```

**Common errors caught:**
- Missing `accessibilityLabel` on buttons
- Low contrast text
- Missing form labels

---

### 10.3 Color Contrast Testing

**Tools:**
- Chrome DevTools → Lighthouse → Accessibility audit
- Axe DevTools (browser extension)
- WebAIM Contrast Checker

---

## 11. Common Violations & Fixes

### 11.1 Icon-Only Buttons

**❌ Violation:**
```tsx
<Pressable onPress={handleClose}>
  <Icon name="close" />
</Pressable>
```

**✅ Fix:**
```tsx
<Pressable
  accessibilityLabel="Close"
  accessibilityRole="button"
  onPress={handleClose}
>
  <Icon name="close" />
</Pressable>
```

---

### 11.2 Unlabeled Inputs

**❌ Violation:**
```tsx
<TextInput placeholder="Email" />
```

**✅ Fix:**
```tsx
<View>
  <Text>Email Address</Text>
  <TextInput
    accessibilityLabel="Email address"
    placeholder="Email"
  />
</View>
```

---

### 11.3 Low Contrast

**❌ Violation:**
```tsx
<Text className="text-gray-400 bg-white">Important message</Text>
```

**✅ Fix:**
```tsx
<Text className="text-gray-900 bg-white">Important message</Text>
```

---

### 11.4 Non-Semantic Markup

**❌ Violation:**
```tsx
<View onPress={handleClick}>
  <Text>Submit</Text>
</View>
```

**✅ Fix:**
```tsx
<Pressable
  accessibilityRole="button"
  accessibilityLabel="Submit"
  onPress={handleClick}
>
  <Text>Submit</Text>
</Pressable>
```

---

## 12. Accessibility in CI/CD

**Pre-commit checks:**
- ESLint with jsx-a11y rules
- TypeScript (catches missing accessibility props if typed)

**PR requirements:**
- Manual testing with screen reader (documented in PR)
- Lighthouse accessibility score > 90 (web)

**See:** [14_ci-cd-requirements.mdc](./14_ci-cd-requirements.mdc) for automation details.

