## 14. Summary Checklist

Before shipping a feature:

- [ ] All interactive elements have `accessibilityLabel`
- [ ] Semantic roles assigned (`button`, `link`, `header`)
- [ ] Touch targets minimum 44x44pt (mobile)
- [ ] Text contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
- [ ] Color not sole indicator of meaning
- [ ] Forms have labels and error announcements
- [ ] Tested with VoiceOver (iOS) and TalkBack (Android)
- [ ] Tested with keyboard navigation (web)
- [ ] Focus indicators visible (web)
- [ ] ESLint jsx-a11y passes

---

## Final Note

> **Accessibility is not optional.**
>
> It's a legal requirement, ethical obligation, and product quality standard.
> Fixing accessibility issues after launch is 10x harder than building it in from the start.

**When in doubt:** Test with a screen reader. If you can't use the app with VoiceOver, neither can your users.
